synopses.synopsis: This program was originally a 90-minute variety program called 'The Screen Guild Show', hosted by George Murphy, with music by the Oscar Bradley orchestra, and with John Conte as announcer. Murphy was replaced by Roger Pryor and a 30-minute drama anthology format was adopted , along with the 'Screen Guild Theater' title. The program was sometimes referred to as 'Screen Guild Players', The Gulf Screen Guild Theater', 'The Lady Ester Screen Guild Playhouse', or 'The Lady Esther Screen Guild Players'. During 1942-1947 the show presented radio adaptations of movies, with music by Wilbur Hatch. From 1947-1950 Th program was sponsored by Camel cigarettes and is some times listed as 'The Camel Screen Guild Theater' In 1950 the format was changed to 60 minutes, with music by Basil Adlam and Michael Roy as announcer. (Radio of Old-Time Handbook p.535)
